&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Indian Power System, as well as in other countries, a High Penetration of Wind Power is considered desirable and attempted to circumvent the environmental pollution problem. The highly fluctuating Wind power &amp;amp; its&amp;nbsp;interaction with the slowly-responding Coal Fired Units are to be considered&amp;nbsp;very carefully in the Optimized Power System Planning and Operation&amp;nbsp;exercises undertaken.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this Lecture, the Main Features of the Evolving Smart EHV Transmission&amp;nbsp;Networks and the Two Main Wind Power Generation &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technologies, DFIG and&amp;nbsp;PMSG, will first be briefly described.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Then, the way the Postgraduate Students and Research Scholars should&amp;nbsp;adopt to study and pursue Research in the area of Optimal Power System operation and Planning, including &quot;Integrated Generation-Transmission&amp;nbsp;Expansion Planning with High Penetration of Wind Power&quot; will be suggested&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speaker: Prof R Balasubramanian, Chair, LMAG, Hyderabad Section&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
